<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-084-926  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 084 926.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Business Week  Feb 5 1990 n3144 p59(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>A talk with John Sununu: 'We ought to make changes that help thewhole system.' (White House Chief of Staff) (interview)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Walczak, Lee; Harbrecht, Douglas A.; Carey, John.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>White House Chief of Staff John Sununu and the Bush Administrationfeel that problems plaguing US high-tech industry cannot be solvedby having a single industrial policy for the government.andP;  Sununuadvocates formulating several policies that aid thecompetitiveness of US industry.andP;  Aiding one segment of industry,according to Sununu, negatively impacts foreign competition andthe balance of the domestic economy.andP;  He wants to seeacross-the-board industry revitalization, not a bailout of oneportion of industry.andP;  He advocates tax credits and cuts and warnsagainst prematurely reducing defense spending, which contributeslarge sums every year to the aerospace and computer industries.andO;Sununu also reiterated the Administration's continuing support ofDARPA and Sematech.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     InterviewGovernment OfficialsPolicyComputer industryGovernment FundingHigh technologyElectronic Industry.andO;Feature:   illustrationportrait.andO;Caption:   John Sununu. (portrait)Person:    Sununu, John H. (interviews).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>